originalText.text:
Summer and Star Organizers are so fantastic! Summer is so efficient, quick, and excellent at organizing. She helped me let go of much more than I thought I would. I can finally see all of my purses and clothes in my closet. She also organized all of my papers and files. She is so sweet, and I was blown away by the results!
When your living space is uncluttered, your productivity and your mood become exceptional. Star Organizers is amazing and I highly recommend them!

originalText.text: Summer is the most organized, energetic and fun person to work with.  My sister and I were faced with a monumental task of organizing all of the things that our mother had accumulated in her 93+ years.  From the moment we hired Summer and Star Organizers, our stress evaporated and the process went smoothly and quickly.  We recommend Summer to anyone who has a big organizing project in front of them.  I can not imagine there is anyone better on the entire planet!

originalText.text:
Summer was a pleasure to work with. Professional, well connected, smart, efficient, and priced fairly, something increasingly rare in today's world.

We accomplished a lot working on a huge NY apartment clearing and later a staging of another smaller place. Summer was fun to work with, and I could count on her.

This work all took place in NY while I was in Seattle. We could manage by phone, email and facetime,  just amazing. And the staging/organizing she did was first-rate! Highest recommendation.

originalText.text: Summer is a genius! She organized my closet in a perfect way and was so fast, kind, and super professional! I literally feel purified after the day we spent together. Now I can finally get dressed easily and be able to see everything I own. My closet and drawers look beautiful, and I couldn't be happier with the result! I highly recommend Star Organizers.

originalText.text:
Summer is life changing at any potential task. This happened to be an estate sale with decades of items in the apartment.  It would be a lot to merely empty and throw out, but she managed to help decide what to keep, decide what do donate (charitably and humanely) and decide what can be sold. Her ability to patiently walk through each of those buckets with you is unmatched, cutting through any sentimentality in an empathetic manner and making practical decisions that both honor people and prepare you for the next stage of your life...while playing an integral role in helping sell the apartment by working with all parties seamlessly, to organize and display it for sale. She'll make you money on the items you decide to sell, as well.

There are so many other services she offers which I have used her copious skills for, but this is one that is unusually fraught in terms of context and content and she was a powerful force.
